SCRAPIE - FINLAND: OIE
***********************
A ProMED-mail post
<http://www.promedmail.org>
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
<http://www.isid.org>

Date: Sat, 2 Nov 2002
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: Animal Health Information Department, Office international des
epizooties (OIE) [edited]
<information.dept@oie.int>

Scrapie in Finland
-------------------
(Disease never reported before in Finland).
Information received on 1 Nov 2002 from Dr Jaana Husu-Kallio, Delegate of
Finland to the OIE: One case of scrapie was laboratory detected on 1 Nov
2002 in a 5-year-old female goat routinely slaughtered.
Location of the outbreak: a dairy farm in the province of Western Finland.
Total number of animals in the outbreak: 44 goats and 6 sheep.
The diagnosis was made according to the National Scrapie Control Programme
routine inspection.
No clinical signs of the disease, other than reduced milk production on the
infected animal, have been detected.
Laboratory where diagnosis was made: National Veterinary and Food Research
Institute, Helsinki. The sample was sent for confirmation to VLA Weybridge,
United Kingdom (OIE Reference Laboratory for scrapie).
Diagnostic tests used: ELISA, western blot and immunohistochemistry.
Source of agent / origin of infection: under investigation.
Control measures:
- All sheep and goats in the affected farm will be destroyed on 2 Nov 2002
and tested for scrapie.
- All contact animals and offsprings and parents of the infected animal
will be destroyed and tested for scrapie.
- Quarantine of the infected farm and of all the contact farms.
... Further details will be published in the next issue of Weekly Disease
Information, available on line as from Fri 8 Nov 2002 afternoon (GMT).
